HEADWORD: Concentrative
<hw>Con*cen"tra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Serving or
tending to concentrate; characterized by concentration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A discrimination is only possible by a <qex>concentrative</qex>
act, or act of attention.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concentrativeness</ent>⟦br⟧
